You may use the following theorem, which says that the sum of internal angles of a triangle is equal to $180^\circ$. Also pay attention to (\ref{eq:smartสน}).
\begin{equation*}
\angle XBH+\angle HBC+\angle YBC=\angle ABC+
\angle CBH+\angle HBL+\angle PLC+\angle PLC+\angle CLB=
\angle ABC+\angle ACB
\end{equation*}
Therefore, we have:
\begin{equation*}
\angle ABC+\angle ACB=360^\circ-\angle AHB,\end{equation*}
and since
\begin{equation*}
\angle ECB
 =\angle ABC+\angle ACB
 =360^\circ-\angle AHB=48^\circ,\end{equation*} 
we have
\begin{equation*}\angle ACB=\angle ECB-\angle ECB=48^\circ-32^\circ=\boxed{16^\circ}. \end{equation*>
